    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sanatoriums devoted to the treatment of tuberculosis, usually dating to the 19th and early 20th centuries. The facilities were typically located in a rural environment, with large windows and sunning porches, large enough to house dozens or hundreds of patients.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
